<text id="A7196T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Williams asks W. E. Whiting to send funds for four months salary and travel expenses.
</p> 
</div1> 

</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">
<head>
<name type="recipient">Mr. Whiting</name> 
<name type="place">Staunton, Va.</name> 
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1866-03-05">March 5<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1866</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Sir</salute> 
</opener> 

<p>Please send me the four months salary due starting from Nov. 7<hi rend="super">th</hi> to March 7<hi rend="super">th</hi></p>

<p>Traveling expenses from Greenfield Mass to New Haven $3,35<lb/>
Carriage in New Haven	            			1,00<lb/>
From New Haven to New York				2,00<lb/>
Carriage in Richmond			   		  50<lb/>
Board in Richmond	                       		3,00<lb/>
Express in Richmond	                          	 ,69<lb/>
From Richmond to Staunton				6,00<lb/>
____<lb/>
						       16,54<lb/>
</p>

<closer>
<salute>Very respectfully,</salute> 
<signed>Mary D. Williams</signed> 

</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
